Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation. Russia seems to have taken over everything. The United States is in a state of shock, and with their military badly depleted by the long isolation, they are completely unprepared to take on the new Russian Empire.

Russian forces march in to Washington DC, and Vladimir Putin Jr becomes the new American President, appointing Donald Trump Jr Jr as his Veep.
The US is divided into the R"ussian Empire," which spans from Maine to Miami, and the People’s Republic of California., and the "Other Russian Empire," comprising the left part.
With American resistance at an end, the rest of the world rbecomes rather peaceful for the first time
 The world is now united under a single banner: The Russian Empire. Peace reigns.
